==Description==
'''Level 974''' is a moderately sized, pink-themed house with signs of neglect and decay. The walls and ceilings are warped, sagging from water damage, and exposed pipes run along in poor condition. A noxious odour of organic waste and stagnant water hangs in the air, making exposure deeply unpleasant. In several areas, the moisture and waste buildup have become so severe that entire microbial ecosystems thrive, forming visible colonies in sinks, walls, and other undisturbed surfaces.

Due to its finite size, '''Level 974''' only consists of a few rooms, including two bedrooms, two bathrooms, a living room, a dining room,
and a kitchen. Despite the appalling living conditions, the electricity is fully functional, and the internet connection is unusually powerful. Attempts to determine the source have been unsuccessful.

The entire household is decorated with objects that evoke extreme cuteness or childlike innocence, with plush toys, pastel furniture, and other kawaii decorated items scattered across every room. Many of these objects, however, are in poor condition, usually found torn apart, stained, or cracked. Furthermore, some items may be infested with cockroaches and rats, usually inhabiting the cushions or furniture.
{{Blurimage|file=Kitty.png|caption=An image of '''Kitty''' walking around thinking it's tuff after a larp session.}}
==Entities==
The most notable feature of '''Level 974''' are the two entities that inhabit it: '''Kitty''' and '''Doggie'''. 
===Kitty===
'''Kitty''' is a tall humanoid entity with long, lanky limbs that lack hands or feet. Its skin is matte black, and has a fabric-like texture. Although '''Kitty''' seems to lack any semblance of facial features, it's able to hear, see, and smell the same way most wanderers can.

In contrast to popular belief, '''Kitty''' is not friendly nor curious whatsoever, and will display aggressive hostility if interacted with. '''Kitty''' possess an inflated sense of self-importance, behaving as if anything it does is incredibly important, and as a result, interprets all forms of interaction, ranging from eye contact, conversation, questions, or even close proximity as 
"interruptions." 

According to recovered digital data and interviews, a significant portion of '''Kitty's''' time is spent on the internet doomscrolling, arguing with strangers, and posting aggressive comments under complete anonymity. Experts have noted that '''Kitty''' is much more bolder online, preferring to insult others through a screen until physically approached, at which point it becomes violently "defensive."

When not actively antagonizing others, '''Kitty''' devotes much of its time indulging in the SCP community, frequently posting strange and deeply concerning comments such as "i like scp and slavery." Researchers later discovered that prolonged exposure to the SCP wiki and its surrounding community was the primary cause for '''Kitty's''' aggressive and elitist behaviour, common traits usually found in other SCP users. One notable aspect that differed from the others, however, was '''Kitty's''' harsh reaction to children engaging with SCP, contrasting with members like Dr. Bright. '''Kitty''' responds with open elitism, harassing children for their own interpretations of SCP, and treats any deviation as "disrespect to the source material." This obsessive need to police how others interacted eventually escalated, leading to '''Kitty''' lashing out at the level itself and tearing apart its walls in a fit of rage.
{{Blurimage|file=974-3.jpg|caption=A selfie of '''Doggie'''.}}
'''Kitty''' is responsible for all the structural and sanitary decline within '''Level 974'''. '''Doggie''', the only other known inhabitant of the level, has
stated that '''Kitty''' refuses to clean anything and instead claims to be "doing research on the internet."<ref>Whether this "research" has any purpose remains unknown.</ref> When asked why he didn't clean the house himself, he simply ignored and continued with what he was originally 
doing.
===Doggie===
'''Doggie''', also known as "DoggieDasher," or "RippyDoggy," is a human-like creature with white skin, brown hair, and dull eyes.
'''Doggie''' is skilled at Geometry Dash, widely regarded as one of the best in the game. He beat several of the most difficult levels over the following years, and eventually became the de factor verifier of Slaughterhouse after spaceuk's exposal.

'''Doggie''' can be found in his personal room, contrasting with the rest in terms of cleanliness. He’s currently verifying Grief, an upcoming Top 1 level that serves as the official prequel to Slaughterhouse, and refuses to interact with anyone, including '''Kitty''', until he verifies it. 

'''Doggie''' and '''Kitty''' do not appear to have any meaningful relationship despite sharing the same household. Both entities are aware of one another, yet neither seems interested in the other. Researchers suggested that this arrangement persists only because Doggie stays in his room while Kitty is too preoccupied with the internet to start direct interaction.

